"Human Rights Resolution" Denounced 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today in a signed commentary describes the "Human Rights Resolution" railroaded through the South Korean National Assembly as a parrot's play of the group of the Grand National Party of south Korea. Noting that the GNP, the local spy party of the U.S. which stakes its fate on it, kicked up a dust over "human rights" after the U.S. made an outcry over them, the commentary says: this reminds us of a parrot.
 The GNP has no need to look afar and is not in a position to disparage others over the human rights issue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the reality of south Korea that people have to shed blood and meet an unexpected death at the hand of aggression army soldiers and even a one-time "national assemblyman" has no one to pour out his woes after being beaten by them in broad daylight. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 More than 10 thousand people commit suicide every year and suicides of parents in company with their children are reported in an unbroken chain in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 How can the GNP crow over other's human rights issue, having such worst human rights problem and no grit to solve it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It should be a party having a correct view of the human rights issue and resolving it. If it makes a stir over a matter which is out of question, while failing to solve an issue awaiting a solution, it is no more than a fool. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The GNP should mind its own affairs, not wasting time in taking issue with other's fictitious "human rights problem." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is only too natural that the south Korean people are turning their backs on the GNP for acting as a bugler and marionette of outside forces, not knowing what it must do.

U.S. Urged to Remain True to AA 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- The United States should honestly implement the Armistice Agreement (AA) signed between the two warring parties in the 1950-1953 Korean War and stop the deployment of more troops and combat equipment and halt at once provocations against the other party.
 This was demanded by seven political parties of Nepal including the Nepal Communist Party (United Marxist-Leninist), the Nepal Worker-Peasant Party and the People's Front of Nepal in a joint statement issued on July 27 on the occasion of the 50th anniversary of Korean people's victory in the Fatherland Liberation War. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We demand that the AA be replaced by a peace agreement between the DPRK and the U.S. in conformity with lasting peace and interests of the DPRK and the rest of the world to build a mechanism for peace on the Korean peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We hold that the Korean problem should be settled by efforts of the Korean nation in the spirit of the resolution of the 30th UN General Assembly and the historic June 15 North-South Joint Declaration free from interference of any outside forces.

Hostile Moves against Chongryon Denounced 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- The central committee of the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea on August 3 released a statement sternly denouncing the sinister provocation committed by the Japanese right-wing reactionaries in Niigata under the patronage and instigation of the Japanese authorities. 
Branding it as an unpardonable terrorism seriously threatening the lives and property of the Korean residents in Japan and an intolerable hostile act intentionally committed to create uneasiness and fear in the community of the Koreans in Japan and thus destroy the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) and bitterly denouncing it in the name of the entire Korean working class, the statement continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is an unavoidable historic responsibility of the Japanese authorities and a moral obligation they assumed by the DPRK-Japan Pyongyang Declaration to check all the hostile provocations against Chongryon and Koreans in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese authorities should immediately give up their outdated hostile policy toward the DPRK and fully ensure the legal position of Chongryon and lives and rights of Korean residents in Japan, going by the main spirit of the declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A provocation against the patriotic cause of Chongryon can never pass with impunity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement expressed the belief that the working class of Japan and other countries of the world, who want peace and stability of the world and value justice and truth, would express firm solidarity with the Korean people in their just struggle to check and frustrate the terrorism of the Japanese reactionaries against Chongryon and Koreans in Japan.

Foreigners Visit Polling Stations 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- Diplomatic envoys and officials of foreign embassies here and foreign guests Sunday visited various polling stations in Pyongyang where the election of deputies to people's assemblies at all levels was under way.
 Sika Aho Antti, chief of the Finnish Group for the Study of Works of Comrade Kim Jong Il, said that the visit to the polling station provided an opportunity to see the true appearance of the Korean people single-heartedly united around the leader. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Mohamed Dioue Fofana, secretary general of the African Regional Committee for the Study of the Juche Idea, said that the people's government of the DPRK enjoys absolute trust and support of the popular masses, adding: It is the reality of Korea that everyone devotedly serving the people is becoming a deputy to a people's assembly at different level. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 S. Gungaadorj, chairman of the standing committee of environment and rural development of the state great hural of Mongolia, said that all the electors voted for the candidates, a clear indication of the high political enthusiasm of the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ahmed Amer al Muakkaf, secretary of the people's bureau of the Great Socialist People's Libyan Arab Jamahiriya here, said that his visit to the polling station offered him a chance to see firsthand how fully popular democracy is guaranteed in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Gan Hua, son of the former vice-chairman of the China-Korea Friendship Association, said that his visit to the polling station helped him know well that the government of the dprk is a genuine popular government guaranteeing the working masses genuine freedom and rights. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Genaro Ledesma Izquieta, chairman of the People's Front of Workers,Peasants and Students of Peru, said that he saw every korean pleased and proud of electing people's deputies, noting that he could confirm that the west's propaganda about the DPRK's "human rights issue" is a sheer lie. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Through the elections the korean people have strikingly demonstrated the might of their single-hearted unity around leader Kim Jong Il, he stressed.

Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Visit to Russia Observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- Papers here today observe the 2nd anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's historic official visit to Russia.
 Rodong Sinmun in a signed article says that his official visit to Russia was an epoch-making event as it provided a new landmark for the DPRK-Russia friendship, human cause of peace and the building of a new and just world structure. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK-Russia friendship has favorably developed over the past two years since his historic visit, the article says, and continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il, who has shown particular concern for boosting the DPRK-Russia friendly and cooperative relations since his russia visit, visited the far Eastern Region of Russia in August last year and was a guest at the russian embassy here several times. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Visits of several high-ranking delegations, contacts and exchange have become brisk between the two countries in recent years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Both countries took measures to strengthen the bilateral cooperation in political, economic, cultural and other fields in the spirit of the talks held by their top leaders and on the basis of the dprk-russia joint documents. The vitality of the DPRK-Russia friendship is being strikingly demonstrated as the days go by. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Russian people have made energetic efforts to achieve the stability of the country and national unity and defend the security and interests of the state under the guidance of President V. V. Putin. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Great efforts are being channelled into increasing national defence power, while economy is making progress. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people appreciate the Russian people's positive efforts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A steady development of the DPRK-Russia friendship is entirely in the fundamental interests of the two peoples and their strategic interests and in favour of peace and security in Asia and the rest of the world and the building of a new and just world structure. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people will as ever boost the dprk-russia friendly and cooperative relations in the spirit agreed upon between the top leaders of the two countries and on the basis of the joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The exploits performed by Kim Jong Il in the history of the traditional DPRK-Russia friendship will last forever and the dprk-russia friendship is bound to steadily grow stronger. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson in a signed article says that the exploits performed by the peerlessly great man through his official visit to Russia, a visit that recorded an epochal chapter in the history of the DPRK-Russia friendship and made an outstanding contribution to the accomplishment of human cause of independence, will shine forever in the history.

Sterilizing Paper Developed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- Pyongyang University of Medicine has developed sterilizing paper recently.
 It contains silver mixed with other germicidal matters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It takes 30 minutes to disinfect a liter of water with a square centimeter of sterilizing paper. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It, which is one second to one fourth in the time of sterilization as against various silver disinfectants, can be in safekeeping for a long time.

Large Stockbreeding Farm on Mountains 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- A large stockbreeding farm was built in Kyenam area, Sinwon county, South Hwanghae Province, the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. The stockbreeding farm, with an acreage of over 5,000 hectares on remote mountains, has several stockbreeding and agricultural branch farms.
 It breeds thousands of domestic animals including goats, rabbits and pigs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
It also has a modern milk-processing factory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was in the difficult days of the "arduous march" that the farm was built. People in the province buckled down to the construction of a 40 kilometer-long road and creation of thousands of hectares of grasslands under the slogan "live not for today, but for tomorrow". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also built many goat folds, pigsties, more than 100 dwelling houses and service establishments. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Leader Kim Jong Il guided the work of the farm on the spot on June 17. He was very pleased with the successful construction of the farm. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The province set the target of expanding the farm and is pushing on with the expansion projects.

Election Returns Announced
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- The central election committee for deputies to the 11th Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK today announced a report on the results of the elections for deputies to provincial (municipal), city (district) and county people's assemblies which were held on Sunday.
 According to the results available at the provincial (municipal), city (district) and county election committees, 99.9 percent of the voters registered on the pollbooks went to the polls and 100 percent of the casters voted for candidates for deputies registered at all constituencies, the report notes, and says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Citizens who are staying in foreign countries or working in the far-off seas could not participate in the elections. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 26,650 officials, workers, peasants and intellectuals were elected deputies to provincial (municipal), city (district) and county people's assemblies. Those elected have devotedly worked for the strengthening and development of the Workers' Party of Korea and the people's power, the building of a great prosperous socialist powerful nation and happiness of the people, with absolute worship of leader Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The elections marked an important occasion in further consolidating the DPRK government as a revolutionary power based on the Songun policy by revamping local power organs with able officials who, intensely loyal to Kim Jong Il, have devotedly worked for the party and the leader, the country and the people.

Results of SPA Election Announced
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- The Central Election Committee today announced a report on the returns of the election of deputies to the 11th Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK which was held on Sunday.
 According to the election results available, 99.9 percent of all the voters registered on the pollbooks went to the polls and 100 percent of the casters voted for candidates of deputies to the SPA registered at all the constituencies, the report says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is an expression of all the voters' support and trust in the DPRK government and a manifestation of our army and people's steadfast will to consolidate the people's power as firm as a rock and accomplish the revolutionary cause of Juche under the guidance of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Citizens who are staying in foreign countries or working in the far-off seas could not took part in the election. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the voters turned out as one in the SPA election for prosperity of the country and strengthening and development of the people's power, with high honor and duty as citizens of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Through the election, the voters cemented the singlehearted unity of our army and people around their great leader and fully demonstrated the revolutionary stamina of Songun Korea where the headquarters of the revolution, the perfect unity and socialism represents a common destiny. They also displayed once again the unshakable desire and will to build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation in this land and accomplish the historic cause of national reunification under the Songun revolutionary leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Given in the report is the list of those deputies to the spa elected after examining the election returns presented by election committees of 687 constituencies across the country.

Kim Jong II Elected to SPA
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- The voters registered at constituency no. 649 all went to the polls and 100 percent of them voted for Kim Jong Il, General Secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea said a report on the results of the election of the deputy to the SPA at constituency no. 649 held on August 3 which was released on August 4 by the central election committee for the election of deputies to the 11th SPA of the DPRK. They had been bestowed with the honor of nominating him as a candidate for the deputy to the 11th Supreme People's Assembly.
 This is an expression of the absolute support and trust of all the servicemen and the people in him and a striking manifestation of the revolutionary spirit and indomitable will of them to vigorously advance under the uplifted banner of Songun, single-heartedly united around the party, the report noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il has comprehensively developed and enriched the immortal Juche idea and set forth new original idea and theory indicating the road for the victory of socialism and thus provided the great guiding idea of the revolution in our times. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
He has successfully embodied them and thus helped convert the country into an invincible country powerful in ideology, politics and military terms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He established the state political system putting stress on national defence on the basis of the original Songun idea and developed the People's Army into an ever-victorious strong army of the leader and the party, thus putting them up as the core unit and the driving force of the Songun revolution. This has made it possible for the People's Army to reliably guarantee the cause of national reunification and the revolutionary cause of Juche with arms as the protector of the country and the creator of the people's happiness, displaying its ever-victorious spirit and dignity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He has wisely led the work of enhancing the function and role of the people's power to meet the requirements of the developing revolution in the Songun era so that the people's power of the DPRK could fulfil its mission as the defender of the independent rights of the popular masses, the organizer of creative ability and householder responsible for the people's living. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He has consolidated the single-hearted unity of the revolutionary ranks with the headquarters of the revolution as its core and aroused the whole party, the whole army and the entire people to brave the raging storm of the revolution and bring a new turn in building a great prosperous powerful socialist nation of Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Our republic will throw brilliant rays as the fortress of socialism of Juche, the lodestar of national reunification and the beacon of hope instilling conviction of victory and courage into the world progressives aspiring after independence as it holds in high esteem Kim Jong Il at the head of the party and the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Central Election Committee reports that Kim Jong Il, General Secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea has been elected a deputy to the SPA according to the polling results confirmed and presented by the election committee of constituency no. 649 for the election of a deputy to the 11th SPA of the DPRK.

DPRK Foreign Ministry Spokesman on Six-Party Talks
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- Six-party talks for a solution to the nuclear issue between the DPRK and the U.S. will be held in Beijing soon thanks to the former's initiative and peaceful efforts.
 In this regard, a spokesman for the DPRK Foreign Ministry today released a statement, which said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We have already clarified several times the stand that the DPRK will not stick to any format of talks if the U.S. is ready to make a switchover in its policy towards the DPRK since it is essential for solving the nuclear issue between the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the recent DPRK-U.S. contacts in New York, we put forward a bold proposal for starting six-party talks in Beijing without going through an unnecessary phase and holding the bilateral talks within their framework. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is an expression of our utmost magnanimity as the proposal has come from the stand to solve the nuclear issue between the two countries peacefully through dialogue in any case. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. side agreed to the DPRK-proposed six-party talks, giving up its persistent assertion that the DPRK should "scrap its nuclear program before dialogue." And it proposed to have DPRK-U.S. contacts within the framework of the talks, at which the two sides will clarify each other's stand and discuss the issue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We have decided to take note of this proposal of the U.S. side. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As the multilateral talks are slated to take place as called for by the U.S. side so far, the forthcoming talks will clearly show the world community whether the U.S. has a true willingness to make a switchover in its policy towards the DPRK or not.

Kim Yong Nam Meets Mongolian Delegation
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, President of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, met and conversed with the delegation of the State Great Hural of Mongolia led by S. Gungaadorj, chairman of the standing committee on environment and rural development of the State Great Hural, at the Mansudae Assembly Hall today.
 The head of delegation said that while visiting a polling station for the election of deputies to people's assemblies at different levels they clearly realized the Korean people are single-heartedly united around leader Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Mongolian government and people are sincerely rejoiced over the fact that the Korean people are successfully pushing forward socialist construction despite difficulties and ordeals under the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il, true to the behest of President Kim Il Sung, he noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He hoped that the Korean people would achieve great success in socialist construction and the cause of national reunification, pursuant to the Songun policy of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Jo Kyu Il, deputy to the Supreme People's Assembly, who is chairman of the DPRK-Mongolia Friendship Parliamentary Group and Janchivdorjyn Lombo, Mongolian ambassador to the DPRK.
